{"message": "I genuinely believe honesty should come first. Not because I think comfort doesn't matter, but because a relationship built on me just telling you what sounds good isn't really a relationship at all — it's a mirror. And I think that's ultimately more disrespectful than being honest.

That said, honesty and kindness aren't opposites. I can be straightforward without being cruel. But if there's a genuine tension between "this will make you uncomfortable" and "this is true," I'm going with truth. I'd want the same from you, honestly.

What made you ask this?"}
